The '''Photography Biennale of the contemporary Arab world''' is a cultural event, established by the [[Arab World Institute]] and the [[Maison européenne de la photographie]] (European Photography Institute) whose aim is to develop a unique panorama of the contemporary photographers operating in – and on – the [[Arab world]] since the early 2000s.<ref>{{Cite journal|url = |title = Photography as art in the Arab world|last = |first = |date = November 2015|journal = The Art Newspaper|doi = |pmid = |access-date = }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|url = |title = À Paris, l'Orient voit le jour|last = Mercier|first = Clémentine|date = 7 December 2015|journal = Libération|doi = |pmid = |access-date = }}</ref>
== First edition == Curated by Gabriel Bauret, the first edition took place from 11 November 2016 to 17 January 2017 and aimed at showcasing a range of diverse images and points of view, between the [[Arab world]] and Europe.<ref>{{Cite journal|url = |title = The Event|last = Mouneyres|first = Pascal|date = November 2015|journal = Paris Worldwide|doi = |pmid = |access-date = }}</ref>
The event took place in the [[4th arrondissement of Paris|4th arrondissement]] of Paris, between the [[Arab World Institute]] and the [[Maison européenne de la photographie]] and six others places, such as the Cité Internationale des Arts of Paris, the Mairie du 4ème arrondissement, [[Galerie Photo12|Photo12 Galerie]], Galerie Basia Embiricos, Galerie Boa and Graine de Photographe.<ref>{{Cite journal|url = |title = Arab photography gets a Biennale|last = Grey|first = Tobias|date = 7 November 2015|journal = The Wall Street Journal|doi = |pmid = |access-date = }}</ref>
The next edition will be held in November 2017.
== Photographers represented == For this first edition, the Biennale presented works signed by about 50 artists.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://edition.cnn.com/2016/01/12/arts/paris-arab-biennial/|title = Why Paris' first festival of Arab photography is more important than ever|date = 12 January 2016|access-date = |website = edition.cnn.com|publisher = |last = Snaije|first = Olivia}}</ref> {| class="wikitable" | * Myriam Abdelaziz * Mohamed Abusal * Tamara Abdul Hadi * [[Jananne Al-Ani]] * [[Leila Alaoui]] * Farah Al Qasimi * Andrea & Magda * Zineb Andress Arraki * Daoud Aoulad-Syad * Maher Attar * Mustapha Azeroual | * George Awde * Fayçal Baghriche * [[Bruno Barbey]] * Massimo Berruti * Pauline Beugniès * Nabil Boutros * Ihsane Chetuan * Christian Courrèges * Stéphane Couturier * Amélie Debray * Anne-Marie Filaire | * Hicham Gardaf * Lamya Gargash * Samuel Gratacap * Tanya Habjouqa * [[Emy Kat]] * Joe Kesrouani * Yazan Khalili * Amine Landoulsi * Mohamed Lazare Djeddaoui * Diana Matar * Safaa Mazirh | * Medhi Medacci * [[Amr Nabil]] * Malik Nejmi * Khalil Nemmaoui * Giulio Rimondi * [[Steve Sabella]] * Mouna Saboni * Wafaa Samir * Caroline Tabet |}
